The paper deals with communication complexity and query complexity, which are both subfields of theoretical computer science. The use of relaxed partition bounds is a common technique in these subfields, and the paper provides new results related to this technique. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of functions and distributions, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the use of lower bounds, which is a topic in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
